Zusa  
Zusa is building g a fundraising platform that allows users to contribute without having to 
donate any money. Users can simply watch advertisements, ﬁll up surveys, click on links to 
product pages, and share on socials. The platform integrates the advertisements and surveys 
sent over by businesses and product/service-based companies and the users which form the 
market for them.
 
 My Language My Learning
  
My Language My Learning is an Edtech platform which is using machine learning to democra-
tize e-learning, ie. make online education available to anyone across all languages, all ages 
& across varied cognizance and income level
 
Transteg Lifecycle  
Transteg Lifecycle is a technology-based aggregation platform that focuses on solving the 
business operation challenges of ﬁeld-level execution vendors for Telecom, Electricity & City 
Gas ﬁeld asset deployment and operations. The platform is a collaborative asset database, 
updated through monitored workﬂows run on web / mobile app. It is offered to vendors on a 
SAAS model - Hosted platform as a service with Disaster recovery & Security framework
 
Aumsat
  
Aumsat is using AI-enabled hydrological analytics derived from Satellite images to enable 
public utilities to accurately forecast and detect water leakages in water transmission 
networks without physically being present on the ﬁeld. Unlike costly, time-consuming, labor, 
and hardware-intensive surveying methods like acoustics, sensor grids, and gas injection 
used for pipeline water leak detection, their technology provides an accurate non-destructive 
method to locate the exact time, location, and extent of pipeline water leakages on a real-time 
basis.
 
SocieTree  
SocieTree is a SaaS integrated social networking platform that empowers nonproﬁts while 
redeﬁning the way the social sector functions. The platform allows nonproﬁts to hire skilled 
volunteers, collaborate with similar organizations, manage their employees, and engage with 
their audiences, thus proving to be a one-stop destination for all their requirements.
 
Shop Local, Shop by store
 
Shop Local, Shop by the store is providing a marketplace for ofﬂine stores to list their prod-
ucts, optimize inventory, and tools to increase their revenue by marketing their products.  The 
solution allows consumers to search across the inventory of the local stores.
30

DocBot
  
DocBot is a Hardware cum SAAS-based company that aims to save 60% of the medical 
consultancy time. Their solution helps in saving time by taking primary vitals (temperature, BP, 
heart rate, O2 level) within seconds through their proprietary hardware device and the saas 
platform allows retrieving the medical history of the patient within 2 minutes.
 
BlisCare
 
BlisCare is an Edutech start-up that aims to provide affordable digital classroom solutions for 
the visually impaired students with Digital Braille Display System (Braille Tablet) which can 
replicate in real-time into digital braille in form of Digital Tablet) that will replicate any text, 
graphical diagram/map to standard Braille, at affordable cost and at the same time it reduces 
cost burden of current education technology by half and at the same time provides unlimited 
content available (online & ofﬂine) which is currently not accessible to the visually impaired 
community.
 
Mauka
 
Mauka is a community ﬁrst professional product for India's blue/grey collar workers helping 
them ﬁnd hyperlocal jobs, upgrade their existing skills, earn skill badges & build professional 
connections. It's the perfect blend of Naukri + Udemy + Linkedin for Bharat.

has a higher  rate in developing  countries  [i.e., India  
up to 37%] where  the major  part is contributed  by 
Air, touch -based  cross -infections . There  is open  
direct -air contact  between  patients  at hospitals  due to 
multiple  patients  treated  in the same  room . We can 
not treat diﬀerently  infected  infectious  disease  
patients  in the same  room  at the healthcare  facility,  
we have  to create  new wards  for every  new type of 
infectious  disease .
SOLUTION
ICU - Isolation  Bed is a transparent  and airtight  
chamber  that has both side a 3-stage  ﬁltration  system  
& air sterilization  process  inbuilt  and the whole  unit is a 
mobile  unit. It provides  individual  patients  isolation  at a 
healthcare  facility . Hence,  completely  prevent  the 
chances  of cross -infection  spreading  via Air, touch,  or 
Vector -borne  from other  patients  or from hospital  staﬀ.

pressurized  as per the need  so for all communicable  
disease  patients .

Uncontrolled  bleeding  is still one of the leading  
causes  of preventable  death  in military  combat  and 
the second  cause  of death  in civilian  trauma  victims  
due to the absence  of eﬀective  & aﬀordable  
hemostats . We’re  lacking  eﬀective  and eﬃcient  
solutions  for controlling  bleeding  in emergency  
situations  which  is one of the leading  causes  of 
preventable  deaths  worldwide .
SOLUTION
StopBleed  is a ﬁbrous  aggregate  having  structural  
and functional  similarities  with ﬁbrin  strands,  a protein  
formed  by the body  to stop bleeding  and heal 
wounds . It achieves  hemostasis  through  its ﬁbrous  
morphology . StopBleed  has a very high absorption  
capacity  which  brings  the blood  components  closer  
together  helping  the body  to accelerate  the normal  
blood -clotting  cascade . It also creates  a hydrogel  at the 
application  site. When  in contact  with a bleeding  
wound,  it rapidly  absorbs  the plasma  and 
concentrates  the erythrocytes  and platelets  at the 
injured  site, leading  to rapid  hemostasis .

financial assistance to startups for proof of concept, prototype development, product trials, market entry and commercialisation. Under this program, DLabs has till date received close to 230 applications of which 27 startups were shortlisted to pitch to the Incubator Seed Management Committee (ISMC) after the initial internal screening and evaluation. These 27 startups presented ventures to the ISMC and the Committee approved funding to 14 startups evaluating and scoring them as per the parameters shared by the startup India team in the Scheme guidelines. Of these 14 startups, 12 startups were funded with INR 25,00,000 as a Convertible Note investment and 2 startups were approved for a Grant of INR 10,00,000.

term sheets and investment agreements for the funding andwill soon be on-boarded into the cohort formally, subject to clearing the due diligence and agreeing to the execution of the terms of the agreements.

Will my startup get funding?
A Machine Learning Model
Anupam Purwar1*and Bhagwan Chowdhry2*
1PGP Alumnus, Indian School of Business, Gachibowli,
Hyderabad, 50032, TS, India.
2*Professor of Finance, Indian School of Business,
I-Venture @ ISB, Hyderabad, 500032, TS, India.
*Corresponding author(s). E-mail(s): bhagwan@isb.edu;
Abstract
We develop a machine learning model that predicts whether a start-
up that has secured no or some initial (seed/angel) funding will
get the next round of investment. Previous work on this topic has
primarily attempted mining databases of the startup ecosystem con-
sisting of investors, incubators and startups. Also, use of web-based
open sources to derive signals for the startup success prediction task
has been investigated, but signals picked were limited to direct men-
tions in the form of web links. We gathered data of 5000+ startups
over a period of 4 years. We used structured data about the startup
founders, team size, product offering, industry sector, funding raised so
far, as well as textual information about their company. Using these
data fields, we trained a machine learning model with multiple fea-
tures using random forest technique. We show that utilizing companies’
textual data on their product offering/business plan provides a sub-
stantial performance boost in comparison to only using structured data
about the startup ecosystem. We provide an in-depth analysis of the
developed machine learning (ML) model as well as different ML tech-
niques experimented to provide a quantitative comparison among them.
This has helped us obtain insights into easily discoverable quantita-
tive signals as well as market factors influencing the startup funding.
Keywords: Predictive modelling, Structured data, Text Analysis, Random
Forest
1

CODE 2023
2 Startup Success
1 Introduction
Startups are integral part of the economy [1, 2] . Many startups use Angel/Ven-
ture capital funds to scale themselves and bring their products to market.
Startup’s ability to survive depends on whether they will be able to raise funds
or not. We have devised a Machine Learning (ML) model to predict whether
a startup would be able to raise funds or not.
2 Methods
We have developed an end to end framework consisting of Data gathering,
Exploratory analysis as well Model development and deployment as a web
service, as shown in Fig. 1.
Fig. 1 : Machine Learning Workflow: Data analysis to Model Deployment
3 Discussion
We gathered data of 5400 startup companies over 4 years capturing startup
founders, team size, product offering/business, industry sector, funding raised
so far in the form of quantitative and textual information. Using these data
fields, we experimented with various machine learning (ML)techniques, as
shown in Table 1. Through this experimentation, we found that random forest
technique provides the best accuracy estimates in terms of Recall, Precision
and Area under the curve (AUC) score with a balanced dataset. All the ML
techniques fail with the actual/imbalanced dataset, with AUC score of approx-
imately 0.5 (refer Fig. 2 and Table 1) . One of the most important observation is
that utilizing companies’ textual data on their product offering/business plan
provides a substantial performance boost in comparison to only using struc-
tured data about the startup. To derive the most valuable information in the

CODE 2023
Startup Success 3
textual description of the startup, we broke the textual information into mul-
tiple quantitative feature vectors and bringing these features into the model
improved the recall of Random forest model from 0.62 to 0.83 (refer Fig. 3).
Besides, a Random forest based classification model, we have also devised a
startup score predictor which calculates a score on scale of 0 to 1 (1-Success,
0-Failure). For the same, we have used the most important features from the
Random forest model to calculate a weighted score for a startup.
(a) Actual Dataset
 (b) Balanced Dataset
Fig. 2 : Outcome Label Histogram: Actual and synthetically balanced dataset
4 Results
We demonstrate that whenever dealing with highly imbalanced dataset, bal-
ancing helps improves the accuracy of model. In the context of startup
companies where a lot of quantitative information related to their financial per-
formance and financial indicators is not available, use of textual information
and its conversion into quantitative feature vectors can tremendously improve
the predictive power of ML models. We have deployed our ML model as a web
service which is accessible to public here: https://tgs-shortlisting.herokuapp.
com/. This service can help predict success/failure score of multiple startups
in one go once data is uploaded as a .csv file.
Acknowledgments. The authors would like to thank I-Venture at ISB for
facilitating this research work. Special thanks to Saumya Kumar for help with
the data gathering exercise. Last but not the least, authors would like to thank
everyone who provided feedback as well as help with experimentation work in
this research.
